==English==

===Etymology===
First attested from [[w:1300|1300]],  from [[Old French]], from [[merveillos]], from [[merveille]] ''a wonder''. See also: [[marvel]].

===Adjective===
'''marvelous''', '''marvellous'''
# Exciting wonder or surprise; astonishing; wonderful.
:I went to a '''marvelous''' party 
:With Nounou and Nada and Nell, 
:It was in the fresh air 
:And we went as we were 
:And we stayed as we were 
:Which was Hell.
Noel Coward: [http://www.lyricsandsongs.com/song/474759.html]

